#compdef claude
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Zsh completion for Claude Code CLI
#
# Generated for Claude Code v2.1.158 by exploring the binary directly
# (`claude <cmd> --help` for every command/subcommand, plus the embedded
# command/option registrations and value enumerations inside the native
# build), then cross-checked against the official CLI reference
# (code.claude.com/docs/en/cli-reference). The binary is the source of truth;
# the docs surfaced commands/flags that are hidden from `claude --help` but
# present in 2.1.158 (background-session commands, --bg/--exec/--remote, etc.),
# each of which was re-verified against this binary before being included.
#
# Structure: a recursive `_arguments -C ... '*::arg:->args'` state machine.
# The `*::` (double-colon) rest-arg spec slices the matched command word out of
# `$words` at each level, so every `_claude_<cmd>` function sees its own
# subcommand as `$words[1]` and its positionals start at spec index `1`.
#
# Commands the binary hides from its own `--help` (remote-control/rc,
# import-conversations, daemon, and the background-session commands
# attach/logs/respawn/rm/stop/kill) and command aliases (plugins, upgrade) are
# real and invokable, so the completion lists them too: `claude <TAB>` offers
# EVERY command, not just the documented subset.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------------------

